“I think the real reason there hasn’t been any reform is that he’s afraid of it, he’s truly afraid of it,” the person said of Cuomo. 
 
Cuomo apparently recognized the issue in 2016 when he ordered the inspector general's office to investigate racial disparities in the criminal justice system, but four years later the report still has not been completed and there has been little public discussion of the efforts. 
 
